Date:  31/3/1854
Source:  Richmond-Atkinson Papers
Author:
Vol / Page:  1/146
Edition:  1960
Quote:  It is very impressive to see the close contact of violence and order indicated by  the armed gold escort amidst the busy street of Sydney: a long phaeton with four seats one behind another, with moustachioed men in plain dresses intended for work, with glistening muskets and pistols, and perhaps a lady passenger in the middle, it is I suppose the gold carriage, and a van and rear-guard of horsemen attend this.
Notes:   (J.C.Richmond)

